text: Individual tests can get it wrong but if it's over a long time span and a product has a good reputation it's probably for real

Galkovsky said people should read Pushkin with a pencil in their hand because of how many references there are in his works to texts from Antiquity, French and German literature, etc. but I feel like you need to do the same with H.P. Lovecraft and read with a world atlas in hand.

E.g. in Eugene Onegin even the first words are a reference to a Russian fable about the donkey being the most honest animal and "make yourself respected" in Pushkin's time meant to die so the novel basically starts "my uncle the donkey kicked the bucket", full of jokes like this.
